The command to connect to a server with openssl is `openssl s_client -connect <hostname>:<port>`. The hostname is `tls1.cryptohack.org`, but I had to guess the port number since the challenge doesn't specify it. Since one of the standards is 443 I tried that one and worked.

The flag to set the TLS version to 1.2 is `-tls1_2`. The final command resulted in:

`openssl s_client -connect tls1.cryptohack.org:443 -tls1_2`
